      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 570: `OnInfoListener` calls `stopAudioRecording()` and updates the dialog from the recorder callback. MediaRecorder callbacks are not guaranteed to be delivered on the main thread on all platform implementations, so touching dialog UI here can crash with `CalledFromWrongThreadException`. Marshal the UI update and recorder state transition to the main thread.\n```suggestion\nsetOnInfoListener { _, what, _ -\u003e\n    if (what \u003d\u003d android.media.MediaRecorder.MEDIA_RECORDER_INFO_MAX_DURATION_REACHED ||\n        what \u003d\u003d android.media.MediaRecorder.MEDIA_RECORDER_INFO_MAX_FILESIZE_REACHED) {\n        view?.post {\n            stopAudioRecording()\n            audioRecordDialog?.setMessage(getString(R.string.audio_recording_limit_reached))\n        }\n    }\n}\n```",
