      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 580: The new audio recording path creates and sends an app-owned recording, but it never checks the final file size before sending. `MediaRecorder.setMaxFileSize()` is best-effort and may be ignored or overshoot on some devices, while the existing preference is presented as a hard message size limit. Validate `file.length()` against `getAudioMaxSize()` before `sendFile(f)`, delete the file, and show a clear error if it exceeds the configured limit.\n```suggestion\nif (file.exists() \u0026\u0026 file.length() \u003e 0L) {\n    val maxSize \u003d getAudioMaxSize()\n    if (maxSize !\u003d Long.MAX_VALUE \u0026\u0026 file.length() \u003e maxSize) {\n        file.delete()\n        Toast.makeText(activity, R.string.audio_recording_limit_reached, Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show()\n        return\n    }\n    startFileSend(Single.just(file).flatMapCompletable { f -\u003e sendFile(f) })\n} else {\n```",
